nts2.n: music for movements w/ vicki huang & salt district mayor
nts2.d:
ÈªÉÁæéÁê¶ vicki huang / ÈπΩÂüïÂçÄÈï∑salt district mayor
Èùú‰∏ç‰∏ãÁöÑÊ≠å music for movements is a hybrid vinyl-CD mix recorded live at ÊΩÆÈõª Chao Bar&RecordStore in Taipei. Presented by ÈπΩÂüïÂçÄÈï∑ Salt District Mayor ‚Äî an audiovisual archive and label devoted to Taiwanese roots music ‚Äî the mix was originally recorded for my monthly Taiwanese Music History Book Club at Chao Bar. Our September session explored Jeph Lo‚Äôs ALTERing NATIVism: Sound Cultures in Post-War Taiwan, and I was especially moved by the chapter on banned songs.
This set gathers those silenced voices ‚Äî from banned songs and protest anthems to ballads of belonging and hope ‚Äî tracing Taiwan‚Äôs long tradition of using music as a tool for social change. Across Mandarin, Taiwanese Hokkien, and Hakka languages, the mix journeys from campus-folk awakenings and labor anthems to Indigenous blues and anti-nuclear protest songs. Each record is a reminder that peace is not the absence of noise, but the courage to keep singing.
Note: The live mix recorded at Chao Bar was around 40min, so I added a few more tracks digitized from my vinyl collection to extend the mix to an hour length. The Chao Bar mix was also taped on video, so if interested, I could cut a few clips for NTS Radio to share on instagram. Thank you for your time and this opportunity!

In a time where the world‚Äôs horror feels unbearable, we find ourselves hovering above our own lives, searching for peace ‚Äî for presence, for inner stillness. We try to give ourselves space, yet the phone remains an extension of the body, a portal into endless waves of dopamine and noise.
The world‚Äôs horror flows through the same channels that keep us hooked: the sharing frenzy, the endless scroll, the social media empire that pulls us deeper into itself.
This mix is a search for peace within that chaos.
May the outside noise pause for a moment, so the voices inside ‚Äî carrying both unrest and peace ‚Äî can guide us to move when the time arrives: first for ourselves, and then for the world.

Observer: a documentary collage of Tehran‚Äôs daily life‚Äîpeople talking in taxis, streets alive with footsteps and calls, field recordings from rides and walks‚Äîblended with modular and granular textures. A blurry dream where we observe and feel everything, but can‚Äôt change what unfolds. My personal story of trying to live peacefully in chaos.

Ascha explores peace as a feeling that is increasingly disillusioning and fragile, and with an undertone of hypocrisy. Her mix is an ambient soundscape which celebrates nature, the sea, the sun and bumblebees - or a drone - and what other sounds do we choose not to hear when we enjoy our peace?

A meditation on peace through contemporary lusophone music that reflects community and shared experience. An hour of sounds from Cape Verde, Guinea-Bissau, S√£o Tom√© e Pr√≠ncipe, Angola, Mozambique, Portugal and Brazil.

nts2.n: One step at a time w/ Leo
nts2.d:
My daily commute is a chaos of work, school, studies and trying to spend time with my friends and family but unfortunately not everything is possible. 
In the midst of trying to figure it all out, these songs gave me a feeling of solace.
The peace of an autumn sunset comes on simple and sure. Nothing is hurried and nothing is lost. It's called Cycladic.

nts2.n: Universal Harmony Mixtape w/ Mild To Wild
nts2.d:
Peace is not about a music genre or a vibe ‚Äî it‚Äôs about harmony. And harmony is inseparable from music.
Peace is also a place ‚Äî a space where everything can exist without harming other beings.
This is a journey into what peace means to different artists, in different moments of the world and of their own existence, all different, all the same.

the moment when you're waking up and your brain is still quiet, right before the day begins. we arrive from a peaceful sleep into collision with whatever today's world will bring. in that peaceful place, where fears/worries/wars don't live. then it's just another day‚Ä¶

the good kind of nowhere, watching the day like it's someone else's problem, presence without eye contact. half-unpacked with nowhere to be, still carrying yesterday's sun in your shoulders. keep it smooth

nts2.n: THE AESTHETICS OF EASE W/ PLUMDOSE
nts2.d: A celebration of simple, profound moments of serenity, in which emotions are conducted by the unobtrusive orchestra of the senses and the mind is uneventful. Dancing colors of soap bubbles. Fabric swaying in tender winds. Fingers gliding along wrapped arms. First bite of an orange. The sound of rolling pebbles underwater. Sleeping spirits of the room.
